: "interface.interface.InterfaceMeta.verify", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check whether a type implements `self`.\n\n# Parameters\n\n[type]\n\n: The type to check.\n\n# Raises\n\nTypeError\n\n: If `type_` doesn't conform to our interface.\n\n# Returns\n\nNone\n"]}, {"name": "interface.interface.InterfaceMeta._invalid_implementation", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "t", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "missing", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mistyped", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mismatched", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make a TypeError explaining why `t` doesn't implement our interface.\n"]}, {"name": "interface.interface.InterfaceMeta._format_missing_methods", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "missing", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.InterfaceMeta._format_mismatched_types", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mistyped", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.InterfaceMeta._format_mismatched_methods", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mismatched", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Metaclass for interfaces.\n\nSupplies a `_signatures` attribute.\n"]}, {"name": "interface.interface.Interface", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "interface.interface.Interface.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.Interface.from_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "existing_class", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "subset", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create an interface from an existing class.\n\n# Parameters\n\nexisting_class\n\n: The type from which to extract an interface.\n\nsubset\n\n: List of methods that should be included in the interface.\n  Default is to use all attributes not defined in an empty class.\n\nname\n\n: Name of the generated interface.\n  Default is `existing_class.__name__ + 'Interface'`.\n\n# Returns\n\ninterface\n\n: A new interface class with stubs generated from `existing_class`.\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "interface.interface.Interface._INTERFACE_IGNORE_MEMBERS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base class for interface definitions.\n\nAn interface defines a set of methods and/or attributes that should be\nprovided by one or more classes, which are called \"implementations\" of the\ninterface.\n\nClasses can declare that they implement an interface `I` by subclassing\n`implements(I)`. During class construction, the base class generated by\n`implements(I)` will verify that the new class correctly implements all\nthe methods required  by `I`.\n\nInterfaces cannot be instantiated.\n\n# Examples\n\n**Defining an Interface:**\n\n```python\nclass KeyValueStore(Interface):\n\n    def get(self, key):\n        pass\n\n    def set(self, key, value):\n        pass\n\n    def delete(self, key):\n        pass\n```\n\n**Implementing an Interface:**\n\n```python\nclass InMemoryKeyValueStore(implements(KeyValueStore)):\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.data = {}\n\n    def get(self, key):\n        return self.data[key]\n\n    def set(self, key, value):\n        self.data[key] = value\n\n    def delete(self, key):\n        del self.data[key]\n```\n\n# See Also\n\n{func}`implements`\n"]}, {"name": "interface.interface.ImplementsMeta", "bases": ["type"], "methods": [{"name": "interface.interface.ImplementsMeta.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mcls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bases", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "clsdict", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "interfaces", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.ImplementsMeta.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mcls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bases", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "clsdict", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "interfaces", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.ImplementsMeta.interfaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "interface.interface.ImplementsMeta._interfaces_with_duplicates", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Metaclass for implementations of particular interfaces."]}], "exports": []}]}